  "prompt": "What should I major in?",
  "response": "Choosing a major is a significant decision that can shape your academic and career path. Here are some steps to help you decide:\n\n### 1. **Assess Your Interests and Passions**\n   - What subjects or activities excite you?\n   - What topics do you enjoy learning about or discussing?\n   - Consider your hobbies and extracurricular interests.\n\n### 2. **Evaluate Your Strengths and Skills**\n   - What subjects have you excelled in?\n   - What skills do you possess or want to develop?\n   - Are you more analytical, creative, or interpersonal?\n\n### 3. **Explore Career Goals**\n   - What type of work do you see yourself doing in the future?\n   - Research careers that align with your interests and skills.\n   - Consider the job market and demand for certain fields.\n\n### 4. **Consider Your Lifestyle and Values**\n   - Do you prefer a structured or flexible career path?\n   - What kind of work environment do you thrive in?\n   - Are salary, job stability, or work-life balance a priority?\n\n### 5. **Research Majors and Programs**\n   - Look into the majors offered at your school or desired institutions.\n   - Review course requirements and career outcomes for potential majors.\n   - Talk to academic advisors, professors, or professionals in the field.\n\n### 6. **Experiment and Explore**\n   - Take introductory courses in different fields.\n   - Join clubs, internships, or volunteer opportunities related to potential majors.\n   - Keep an open mind; your interests may evolve over time.\n\n### 7. **Seek Guidance**\n   - Talk to mentors, family, or friends who know you well.\n   - Consider taking career assessments or personality tests (e.g., Myers-Briggs, StrengthsFinder) for insights.\n\n### Popular Major Categories to Consider:\n- **STEM**: Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics\n- **Business**: Finance, Marketing, Management, Entrepreneurship\n- **Healthcare**: Nursing, Biology, Public Health, Medicine\n- **Creative Arts**: Fine Arts, Graphic Design, Film, Music\n- **Social Sciences**: Psychology, Sociology, Political Science\n- **Humanities**: History, Literature, Philosophy, Languages\n\nRemember, your major doesn\u2019t have to define your entire career. Many people change paths or pursue interdisciplinary roles. Focus on what excites and motivates you, and don\u2019t be afraid to explore!",
